gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 120, Raptors 113
gameRecap.excerpt: Phoenix defeats Toronto, 120-113. For Phoenix, Kevin Durant (35 points, three rebounds), Grayson Allen (26 points (eight 3PM), three assists), and Bradley Beal (20 points, eight assists) combine for 81 PTS to lead the way in the victory. Gary Trent Jr. tallied 30 points (five 3PM) and three rebounds with RJ Barrett recording 23 points and four assists while Immanuel Quickley notched his 13th career double-double with 21 points and a career-high 18 assists for Toronto in the losing effort. Phoenix improves to 37-26 on the season, while Toronto moves to 23-39 with the loss.
